Program: Outlook
Title: 28/06/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00trrbb
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 29 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, former East German sprinter Ines Geipel tells how the secret police ended her sporting career with a botched operation when she tried to defect to the West. And the journalist and film-maker who took their learning disabled brother on a road trip to meet his hero, the drummer of the heavy rock band Metallica. (Image: Will, Tom and Kate Spicer (L-R). Credit: Chris Floyd) Show less